(41, 6, 1, 40, 2, 23, 23, 'his own country', 'Connection of Jesus to Nazareth', 'This connection highlights Jesus'' return to his own country, Nazareth, as noted in both passages. Both verses emphasize his identity as a Nazarene, fulfilling the prophetic declaration.', 'prophecy', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 1, 40, 13, 4, 4, 'and his disciples follow him', 'Connection of Discipleship and Sowing', 'This connection highlights the theme of following and receiving teachings. In Mark, the disciples follow Jesus, while in Matthew, the act of sowing seeds can symbolize the spreading of teachings to those who may or may not receive them.', 'theme', 0.286, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
