(41, 6, 3, 43, 6, 42, 42, 'the son of Mary', 'Jesus'' Identity and Origins', 'Both passages emphasize the familiar origins of Jesus, questioning how he can claim divine authority. The mention of his earthly family in both contexts highlights the skepticism of those who knew him. This connection highlights the tension between his earthly identity and his heavenly claims.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
